(who was rumoured to have
 been courting <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="WOL01">Mary Wollstonecraft </persName>
before her relationship with
Godwin – see St Clair, p. 163 and 173)
 married <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="ALD02">Amelia Alderson</persName>, the novelist, poet and
daughter of a Norwich doctor, 
in 1798.  Godwin had contact with 
both Amelia and John 
(who painted Wollstonecraft’s portrait in 
1797 where she is seen pregnant with Mary). 
 Entries with ‘Opie’ have been coded as 
John, whereas the ‘Opies’ after 
marriage are taken to include both John and Amelia. 
 A A, Mes Opie, etc have been coded as Amelia.</p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> Godwin records his death.</p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Opie appears in the 1796 lists under 1795 which accords with his first appearance in the diary
